 82444 July 15, 1989, Saturday, Home Edition Part 1; Page 26; Column 1; Metro Desk 885 words BID TO EXCLUDE ILLEGALS FROM CENSUS HIT; OFFICIALS SAY MOVE WOULD HURT STATE IN CONGRESS, CUT FEDERAL AID By FRANK CLIFFORD, Times Staff Writer Public officials throughout California have condemned a U.S.
 Senate vote Thursday to exclude illegal aliens from the 1990 census, saying the action will shortchange California in Congress and possibly deprive the state of millions of dollars of federal aid for medical emergency services and other programs for poor people. "I think it's an outrageous piece of legislation and probably unconstitutional," Assemblyman Peter Chacon said Friday.
